{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T12:01:26.905Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Code review"},{"type":"text","text":" is the workflow where Claude checks your changes for bugs, correctness issues, style problems, and missed edge cases before you merge them. In Claude Code, this can happen on local diffs or on a GitHub pull request, and the output is typically a structured set of findings with file and line references."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Does"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude can review code in a few different ways:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local review"},{"type":"text","text":" of your staged or unstaged changes before pushing.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"PR review"},{"type":"text","text":" after code is already on GitHub.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Targeted review"},{"type":"text","text":" focused on tests, error handling, types, documentation, or security.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Automated review"},{"type":"text","text":" that posts findings directly as PR comments."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The main goal is to catch issues early so humans can focus on higher-level judgment instead of mechanical checks."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Typical Review Flow"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Prepare changes"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Stage files or point Claude at a PR/diff."}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Ask for review"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run a review command or prompt for a code review."}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Inspect findings"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude reports bugs, risks, and improvement ideas with references."}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. Fix issues"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Update the code and rerun the review to verify the fixes."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Claude Looks For"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A good review usually checks:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Correctness bugs"},{"type":"text","text":" and logic errors.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Security issues"},{"type":"text","text":" and unsafe assumptions.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test coverage gaps"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Type consistency"},{"type":"text","text":" and API misuse.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Documentation and clarity"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simplification opportunities"},{"type":"text","text":" where code is too complex."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"AI-written code can move fast, but review is what keeps that speed from turning into technical debt. Review helps catch issues before merge, when they are cheapest to fix, and it reduces the chance that fragile or incomplete code reaches production."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Useful Patterns"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run review before creating the PR"},{"type":"text","text":" to catch obvious issues early."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use focused review prompts"},{"type":"text","text":" when you only want tests, docs, or security checked."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rerun review after fixes"},{"type":"text","text":" to confirm the problems are gone."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Keep a checklist"},{"type":"text","text":" in your project conventions so Claude reviews against your team’s standards."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Code review with Claude is fast and consistent, but it is not a replacement for human judgment. It is best at spotting mechanical or pattern-based problems, while humans still need to evaluate architecture, product intent, and trade-offs."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of Claude Code review as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"first-pass reviewer"},{"type":"text","text":". It is the teammate that catches the obvious bugs, points out weak spots, and summarizes what deserves attention before the code reaches a human reviewer."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Code review in Claude Code checks changes for bugs, risks, and quality issues."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It can review local diffs or GitHub pull requests."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The best workflow is review → fix → review again."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It is most valuable for catching mechanical issues early."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Human review still matters for architecture and product judgment."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
